description.narrative:
Summary will be available soon.The application aims to contribute to the reduction of transmission of COVID 19 through effective identification of active transmission chains. 
Specifically, the project will: 
Increase access to COVID 19 detection services for the vulnerable populations; 
Improve capacity of responders in case identification, reporting and response to COVID 19;  
Improve operational presence of WHO in the high burden districts for effective response support to the COVID 19 outbreak. With CERF funds, WHO will ensure availability of COVID 19 testing commodities; support on Risk based testing, surge deployments, active case findings and contact tracing; and ensuring availability of services for displaced families through emergency outreaches in the displaced camps and in the hard to reach distant locations in affected sub counties.

The interventions are expected to expand access to testing services for 30,000 primary beneficiaries in the country.
